<HEADLINE>Soldier, 18, found dead near base</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>2</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975159345</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
AN 18-year-old soldier was found dead with a single bullet wound to her head
near an Army base yesterday.
Private Cheryl James was discovered lying in woodland about 90ft outside the
garrison in Deepcut, Surrey, where she was on patrol. Her rifle was lying
beside her.
Police said they were not looking for anyone in connection with her death.
Private James, from Llangollen, Clwyd, was a member of the Royal Logistics
Corps.
She had been serving at the garrison since joining the Army in July and was
single.
A joint investigation by Surrey police and the Royal Military Police was
launched after her body was found.
An Army spokesman said a post-mortem examination would be carried out today.
The incident happened five months after a 20-year-old guard shot himself dead
at the barracks.
Private Sean Benton, of Hastings, East Sussex, killed himself hours after being
told he was being discharged from the Army.
An inquest heard that he could not cope with the shame of being ordered out of
the Army.
An Army spokesman said there was no connection between that incident and
Private James's death.
</TEXT>
