<TEXT>
Paging Kenny Dalglish: the Scottish connection may be obvious, but when world
snooker champion Stephen Hendry, and the most capped footballer in Scotland's
history, Kenny Dalglish, usually meet socially, the green is the grass of a
golf course rather than the baize.
Pro-am tournaments, we are told, are graced regularly by their attendance.
Yesterday, however, the Blackburn Rovers' director of football took time out to
help pal Hendry launch his new book in Preston, as well as give him support as
he defends the UK snooker championship at the Guild Hall.
And let's face it, the idea of someone signing his name on the dotted line is
not unusual for Dalglish.
