<TEXT>
City fete
EVENTS and entertainments costing more that #250,000 have been programmed for
Aberdeen's senior citizens and disabled next year by the district council.
Events include a dinner party for more than 10,000 people in the Beach Ballroom
at a cost of #150,000, a day of festivities for the 800 blind people in the
city, and a disco and cabaret evening for young disabled people.
Flume repair
ABERDEEN District Council faces a bill of #150,000 for repairs to the water
flumes at the city's Beach Leisure Centre. The flumes, made by Whitewater
Leisure Ltd, have been out of commission since June.
