<DOCNO>GH951128-000041</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH951128-000041</DOCID>
<DATE>951128</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Macari escapes FA ban</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>37</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975159383</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
STOKE City manager Lou Macari yesterday escaped with a warning after the
Football Association found him guilty of rude remarks to a referee.
The former Celtic manager was charged with bringing the game into disrepute
after he confronted Worcester official Gerald Ashby at half-time in Stoke's
Coca-Cola Cup tie against Newcastle on October 25. Ashby had sent off Stoke's
Ian Cranson following two bookable offences.
A spokesman for the FA said: ``Lou Macari has been severely censured and warned
as to his future conduct. He has also been ordered to give a written
undertaking that he will not repeat the offence and must pay part of the costs
of the hearing.''
Last week the FA decided to take no action against Wimbledon manager Joe
Kinnear following his reported criticism of referee Paul Alcock, who sent off
Vinnie Jones against Nottingham Forest.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
