<HEADLINE>TAX EXPERT.  Jill offers route through maze</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>25</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975159385</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
PEOPLE in Sutherland looking for a way through Chancellor Kenneth Clarke's tax
maze Budget are being offered a helping hand by a new business venture.
With the aid of a business start-up package from Caithness and Sutherland
Enterprise, tax expert Jill Gordon has set up the area's first specialist
consultancy aimed at businesses and the general public.
A member of the Association of Taxation Technicians and an associate of the
Chartered Institute of Taxation, Ms Gordon has more than 25 years' experience
in her field.
She said: ``Tax can be a nightmare for people and it is easy to get confused
and end up making costly mistakes. There are major changes coming into the tax
system in 1997 when we all have to deal with the new rules for self-assessment.
``This is the biggest change in the UK system in 50 years and I think it will
hit the self-employed the hardest.
``Bearing in mind the large number of self-employed in the area and the current
lack of specialist advice to businesses in general, I felt there was an
opportunity to put my expertise and experience to good use.
``Chartered Accountants have traditionally done this kind of work but most
firms are too small to have a taxation expert on their staff for such a
specialised field so I won't be competing with them.''
Ms Gordon will be offering advice on all aspects of tax, especially income tax
and PAYE, also corporation tax, capital gains tax, inheritance tax, VAT and
stamp duty.
As well as having financial assistance from CASE, Ms Gordon has also taken part
in a series of business start-up skills courses hosted by the enterprise
company, part of the Highlands and Islands Enterprise network.
Alistair Kennedy, who is head of business development for CASE and is based at
the enterprise company's new office at Golspie, said: ``I don't think any of us
like paying tax but it is a fact of life.
``What Jill Gordon will be doing is helping individuals and businesses through
the taxation maze thus providing an important new addition to the range of
professional services available in Caithness and Sutherland.''
</TEXT>
