<DATE>951128</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Serbs `in nervous mood'</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>8</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975159405</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
q FRENCH Foreign Minister Herve de Charette said in Barcelona tonight the peace
deal initialled in Dayton, Ohio, last week between Bosnia, Serbia and Croatia
would probably be signed in Paris in the second week of December.
De Charette said he had discussed the timing in a telephone call with US
Secretary of State Warren Christopher and expected they would agree to set a
final date tomorrow.
The Muslim-led Bosnian government, and international negotiators who helped
broker the deal, have made it clear US participation in the peace force is
crucial to the success of the whole package.
The Serbs are incensed that Sarajevo suburbs they hold will revert to the
control of the new Muslim-Croat federation under the terms of the accord, and
have threatened carnage.
United Nations officials in the capital said Serbs were ``very, very nervous''
about the changes, and warned of a possible mass exodus from the
districts.-Reuter.
</TEXT>
