<TEXT>
QUALIFYING SCHOOL
ALL four Scots left in today's final round of the PGA European Tour Qualifying
School in Spain remain in contention for one of 40 coveted cards.
Only Stephen Gallacher can possibly contemplate a relaxing afternoon at San
Roque on the Costa del Sol while the others sit perilously close to the cut-off
mark of five-over-par.
The 21-year-old from Bathgate is unlikely to sit back following a disappointing
day yesterday when he slipped to a one-over-par 73 as a stiff breeze again blew
competitors off course on the Tony Jacklin-designed venue. ``That was
horrendous,'' was the Walker Cup man's stark assessment of his fifth round
across the testing 7044-yard course.
Raymond Russell atoned well for opening slips, the Longniddry lad covering the
final 10 holes in four under par to complete a fine 71. Scott Henderson (King's
Links) sits one shot behind him on a four-over-par score of 362.
Having lost out on winning his card at the fourth sudden-death play-off hole at
Montpellier last season, William Guy (Buchanan Castle) closed poorly for a
one-over-par 73 and sits on six over par.
South African Fredrick Buhrmann shot a 73 and leads by two strokes from
Englishmen Steve Webster - the winner of the amateur medal at this year's Open
Championship - and Andrew Collison. Leading scores:
350 - H Burhmann (S Africa) 67, 73, 69, 68, 73. 352 - A Collison (England) 69,
70, 71, 73, 69; S Webster (England) 74, 65, 71, 74, 68. 353 - M Wills (Wales)
71, 68, 70, 72, 72. 354 - S Gallacher (Bathgate) 72, 72, 68, 69, 73; T Gogele
(Germany) 67, 76, 68, 71, 72. 356 - P Sjoland (Sweden) 69, 76, 68, 74. 357 - R
Coles (England) 69, 72, 69, 74, 73; A Lebouc (France) 71, 68, 71, 74, 73; D
