<TEXT>
Children burned
in stove accident
FIVE-YEAR-OLD Dean Stewart and his sister Isabella, two, were in stable
condition in hospital yesterday after being badly burned at their home at
Wright Place, Kirkcaldy, on Sunday night.
It is understood that the top came off a canister for an unlit gas camping
stove. Gas was ignited by a coal fire and the flames set the children's pyjamas
ablaze.
Jobs for Arran
FIFTEEN jobs will be created with the opening next July of an #800,000 visitor
centre at the Isle of Arran Distillery, at Lochranza. The project is expected
to attract 50,000 visitors a year.
Walkers well
TWO hill walkers turned up safe and well yesterday after an RAF rescue
helicopter had searched the Cairngorms for them. Mr Mark Adams, 24, and Mr
Simon Metcalfe, 24, of Brandon Street, Edinburgh, had failed to return to their
car at Corrie Cas car park on Sunday evening.
Sex claim report
A TEENAGER is the subject of a report to the procurator-fiscal after Lothian
and Borders Police investigated an alleged abduction and sexual assault by two
men on Friday.
Hotel raid
TWO masked men yesterday forced two female members of staff at the Carlton
Highland Hotel, in North Bridge, Edinburgh, to hand over a three-figure sum of
cash. Neither woman was injured.
#3m Gauguin
A PAINTING by Paul Gauguin showing one of his first impressions of Tahiti in
the 1890s, Femmes Au Bord De La Riviere, sold for #3,191,500 at Sotheby's in
London last night.
Youth jailed
A SHERIFF yesterday heard how one of his own court officers at Falkirk, Mr
David Findlay, 61, was punched by a man who stamped on the roof of his car in
Bo'ness last week. Mark Kerr, 22, of Pennelton Place, Bo'ness, was jailed for
three months.
Journalist dies
THE drowning of a sportswriter at the weekend appears to have been a tragic
accident. The body of Mr Damon Quigley, 30, a freelance writer, of Yorkhill
Street, Yorkhill, Glasgow, was found on the beach at Earlsferry early on Sunday.
Charlie Chester
THE veteran entertainer, ``Cheerful'' Charlie Chester, 82, remained on the
critical list yesterday in hospital at Canterbury, six days after suffering a
stroke.
</TEXT>
