Abattoir raid
POLICE are hunting thieves who stole a large amount of meat from an abattoir at
Brechin in an overnight raid. A Volvo F16 container lorry was also stolen.
Rape charge
MR Frank Hempsell, 42, of Scone, was accused of rape yesterday after an alleged
incident in the Perthshire village on Friday. He made no plea at Perth Sheriff
Court and was released on bail.
Fishing injury
A 15-YEAR-OLD youth suffered a suspected broken leg on the Eyemouth-based
fishing boat Fraiouch Gal, eight miles off the Berwickshire coast. He was taken
to Borders General Hospital.
