<HEADLINE>Nurse is fired over records</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>5</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975159454</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A STAFF nurse at Berwick Infirmary who rewrote medical records following the
death of an 11-month-old baby has been sacked.
The nurse, who has not been named, had been suspended last month. Yesterday,
she was dismissed following a disciplinary hearing conducted by Cheviot and
Wansbeck NHS Trust.
A spokesman for the trust said: ``The panel concluded the nurse had falsified
entries on the casualty card and also attempted to destroy original
documentation which, in their opinion, constituted gross professional
misconduct.''
Ryan Smith, of Dean Drive, Tweedmouth, Berwick, died in a doctor's surgery in
the town where he had been taken by his parents following a telephone call
between the nurse and the family doctor.
There was no-one at the infirmary to examine the baby after he became ill. He
had suffered from a heart defect from birth.
An inquiry team set up by the trust had already concluded that the nurse's
action in rewriting the records had no effect on the outcome.
</TEXT>
