<HEADLINE>Marino record but Miami lose again</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>Steve Livingstone</BYLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>36</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975159472</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
AMERICAN FOOTBALL
THE San Francisco 49ers' NFL resurgence continued with the return of
quarterback Steve Young and a 41-13 rout of divisional rivals St Louis Rams at
Candlestick Park.
Young, out for six weeks after a shoulder injury, looked as if he'd never been
away, throwing for 226 yards and three touchdowns as the Super Bowl champions
topped the NFC West with an 8-4 record. The Atlanta Falcons slumped to 7-5 when
a 28-yard field goal in overtime earned the Arizona Cardinals a 40-37 win.
Quarterback Dan Marino set an NFL record for TD passes - 346 - with four in the
Miami Dolphins' visit to Indianapolis, but the Colts won 36-28.
He has eclipsed three of the legendary Fran Tarkenton's passing records this
season - but each time the Dolphins have lost. They have now slumped to 6-6 in
the AFC East behind Buffalo Bills (8-4), who lost 35-25 to New England
Patriots, and Indianapolis (7-5).
In the AFC Central, Cleveland Browns lost 20-17 to Pittsburgh Steelers, who now
lead the division at 8-4.
Green Bay quarterback Brett Favre threw three touchdowns and running back
Dorsey Levens ran for two more as the Packers thrashed Tampa Bay Buccaneers
35-13 to lead the NFC Central.
Philadelphia Eagles continued their revival, with running back Ricky Watters
rushing for 124 yards and two touchdowns in a 14-7 win over the Washington
Redskins, propelling them to 8-4 and second place behind Dallas (10-2) in the
NFC East.
NFL week 13 results: Atlanta 37, Arizona 40; Carolina 26, New Orleans 34;
Chicago 27, New York Giants 24; Cincinnati 17, Jacksonville 13; Denver 33,
Houston 42; Miami 28, Indianapolis 36; New England 35, Buffalo 25; New York
Jets 16, Seattle 10; Philadelphia 14, Washington 7; Pittsburgh 20, Cleveland
17; St Louis 13, San Francisco 41; Tampa Bay 13, Green Bay 35.
STEVE LIVINGSTONE
</TEXT>
