DONALD Macaulay of Dalilea Farmhouse, Kinlochmoidart, Inverness-shire, has been
appointed to the board of United Auctions, the livestock auctioneer. Mr
Macaulay farms 14,000 acres of hill country carrying 800 blackface and Cheviot
ewes and 140 cross-Simmental beef cows.
PROFESSOR Phil Thomas, principal and chief executive of the Scottish
Agricultural College, has been appointed to the board of the Animal Medicines
Regulatory Training Authority which is responsible for the training,
accreditation and registration of personnel involved in the distribution,
storage and sales of animal medicines.
