<HEADLINE>Japanese face spider scare</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>9</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975159494</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Tokyo, Monday
FEARS that western Japan could soon be crawling with deadly spiders prompted
stock market punters to pounce on insecticide shares today.
Demand was so overwhelming for aptly-named Fumakilla Ltd shares that they
failed to trade in the morning.
But in the afternoon some willing sellers crept out, orders were matched, and
the shares initially surged more than 11%.
The redback spider, native to Australia, has started appearing in Japan's
second city, Osaka.
Local media have quoted health ministry officials as saying that the red-back
spider's bite is fatal in 3!s% of cases, although it has yet to strike in
Japan.-Reuter.
</TEXT>
